rComments: Extremely unclear expectations for assignments. Would not provide me feedback on grades after emailing twice. Went into the exam without marks from previous assignments back. Also, she does not cite her lectures making it very difficult to source things that she talks about (often it is no where to be found)
Kathryn is really knowledgeable. There were a lot of readings, but it was still a really good class. Assignments were super interesting. You will do well you follow her instructions/grading criteria.

Incredible professor and an inspiring person. Her depth of knowledge on the subject matter was astounding and I couldn't wait to learn from her each class. The structure of the class was a bit disorganized, but it didn't detract from the learning for me. This was my favourite class that I've taken during my undergrad. Thank you, Professor Campbell!

Professor Campbell is an incredibly knowledgeable professor and her content is engaging. However, the professor was disorganized and her communication skills with the class was abysmal. She rarely knew what was next in the syllabus, double-booked groups, and expectations were unclear. A simple schedule change took over a week to be communicated.

While knowledgeable, the expectations for the course, especially in terms of final exams, are unrealistic. The amount of readings in this course is the equivalent to 2 courses combined. Grading criteria is also unclear. She is also somewhat aloof as well, especially when talking to students sometimes.

Gives an insane amount of readings (likely because she is a Law professor). Lectures are monotonous, and I dislike how she communicates to students sometimes (she comes off as very standoff-ish at times). She is very knowledgeable however, and lectures are easy to understand and follow. Beware that you must do readings to pass.

I think Professor Campbell is a much better prof than these reviews would make you believe. She is extremely knowledgeable and her lectures are really easy to follow! She's a little scatter brained sometimes but always brings it back to the material without going on too much of a tangent. Would absolutely take again.
she was an amazing prof. she knows what she is talking about and makes class interesting.

Very intelligent and clear with explanations, but monotonous. Midterm and assignment were easy, but TAs werent helpful at all. You should probably buy a textbook just in case. Havent completed final yet, but material is easy to understand and will likely be fine.
She does not respond to students emails, even after saying that she would at the beginning of the semester
Terribly biased and unprofessional. Someone in her position should learn that being respectful is of the upmost importance. I would not recommend any of her classes to anyone!

Very dull lectures, the prof is very knowledgable on the topic.  She told us to study specifics for the midterm, and they were not on it.  Her expectations are vague for the assignment, and grades it quite harshly.  I would not recommend taking the class simply because there are so many better profs & classes to offer than this. Did not learn much
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Had a good understanding into the issues that were brought up in class. Tests were fair, covered the material in the lectures and readings. Overall good prof, would take again.

Her lectures were interesting, she definitely knew her stuff and had a lot of personal stories to back up the material she taught. However, she's not approachable at all. Never smiled, was never available for help when students needed it, seemed like she couldn't care less. Tests and assignments are goodfair if you study. Overall it was decent!

Barely helps when asked questions. SOOO boring to listen to. It's like she doesn't even care about what she's teaching. She's intimidating to talk to because she seems very stand off-ish. Probably saw her smile 3 times. But her exams and assignments are fair and so is her marking.

This professor always seemed scattered and disorganized. There were way too many readings and she contradicted herself on many occasions. Her TA marked the written assignment unfairly, and the prof takes off marks on midterms for the smallest details. Definitely not an easy class, and very difficult to keep up if you write your notes by hand.
Very hard, tons of readings, hard marker, stories drag on, the only interesting thing were the occasional movies shown. When people give their opinions, she kind of brushes them off.

Great class, great professor. She knows a LOT about what she's talking about, the subject matter is interesting, she provides lots of feedback on assignments.  Her lectures are very interesting- lots of movies too, and she's a sweet heart.  I highly recommend her.
Material is very interesting and her stories that relate to the material are fun to hear. Rlly goes by the textbook which is nice but tests and papers - not such an easy mark.
Good prof
